# shared library 
In Jenkins, a Shared Library is a way to reuse common pipeline code across multiple Jenkins jobs 
instead of duplicating the same Groovy scripts in every Jenkinsfile.

#create the folder in GitHub with name name var and create the groovy file
#vars/dockerBuild.groovy
def call(String imageName) {
    sh """
       docker build -t ${imageName}:${env.BUILD_NUMBER} .
    """
}

#Jenkinsfile

Step 1: Install Required Plugin
Shared Groovy Libraries

Step 2: Configure Global Shared Library
Manage Jenkins
 → System
 → Global Pipeline Libraries

 Click Add.

 Eg:

Name: shared-lib
Default version: main
Allow default version to be overridden: ✓ (optional)
Include @Library changes in job recent changes: ✓ (optional)
Retrieval method: Modern SCM

